-- Angola's Unitel Will Spend $800 Million to Expand Services, Angop Reports
-- Brian Latham
-- 2010-06-18T11:07:29Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-18/angola-s-unitel-will-spend-800-million-to-expand-services-angop-reports.html

          
          
             Unitel SA, an Angolan mobile phone
operator, will spend $800 million expanding its services in 2010
and 2011, the state-owned  Angolan Press Agency , known as  Angop ,
said, citing a statement from the company.  
 Unitel will finance the expansion without borrowing, the
Luanda-based news agency said on its website. The company is
targeting 8.5 million customers, Angop reported.  
